body:
Turns out the `fcntl` module [is unavailable on Windows systems](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/1422368/fcntl-substitute-on-windows). In Windows there's an alternative called the `win32api`. But the interface is very different from the `fcntl` library. 

If you're running on windows 10 consider using [Windows Subsystem for Linux](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/wsl/install-win10). I use it quite a bit, especially for these kind of cases where there isn't a suitable alternative that works on Windows.
Thanks @MammadTavakoli & @wmeints for answering the question! Will close this out since the question was answered, but feel free to reopen :)
